    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1869 a railroad line opened, linking Lawrence to New York City and sparking its growth as a commuter hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lawrence%2C_Nassau_County%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Rock Hall Museum, a colonial‑era house, now serves as a museum that showcases Long Island’s early history.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/lawrence/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Old Lawrence, or Back Lawrence, still hosts grand mansions and beachside villas that date back to the American Revolution.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lawrence%2C_Nassau_County%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Lawrence is one of the Five Towns, famed for its wealth, private schools, and historic clubs such as the Rockaway Hunting Club.",
